Peter Dada, Akure A yet-to-be identified man was on Thursday abducted on the Ise Akoko-Isua Akoko Road in the Akoko South-East Local Government Area of Ondo State, while his driver was shot dead. It was gathered that the lifeless body of the driver was found inside the car, while his boss was dragged away into the bush. The case was said to have been reported at the Ikare Akoko Police Station. After the report, the police reportedly moved to the scene of the incident, where the vehicle of the victim was recovered and body of the dead driver taken to a mortuary. The Ikare Akoko Police Area Commander, Razak Rauf, said the police were combing the forest to rescue the victim and arrest the criminals. The corpse of the driver was said to been deposited in the mortuary of the State Specialist Hospital in Ikare Akoko. Copyright PUNCH.
